issues.body:
```
struct {
    rrc_msg_type msg_type;
    select (return_routability_check.msg_type) {
        case path_challenge: Cookie;
        case path_response:  Cookie;
        case path_drop:      Cookie;
    };
} return_routability_check;
```

What are the considerations about that select? For me it looks like all "cases" are the same? Do I oversee something?

```
struct {
    rrc_msg_type msg_type;
    Cookie cookie;
} return_routability_check;
```

comments.body:
I think the current text is already saying what you propose :-)

In the context of the paragraph, there is no "rest of the RRC message" that isn't the "unknown value", so the addition seems redundant to me.

@hannestschofenig WDYT?

Assuming:

```
struct {
    rrc_msg_type msg_type;
    select (return_routability_check.msg_type) {
        case path_challenge: Cookie;
        case path_response:  Cookie;
        case path_drop:      Cookie;
        case path_reset:      uint_8 tag;
    };
} return_routability_check;
```

If `path_reset` is unknown, what is then to be ignored?

Maybe:

> Implementations MUST be able to parse and ignore messages with an unknown `msg_type`.

```suggestion
## Timer Choice {#timer-choice}
```
